In this section, financial viability is explored to determine the sustainability of the suggested method. Several techniques were used with consideration of the main factors affecting the cost of purified water, such as site, fed water quality, system capacity, and price of components (Chaichan and Kazem 2015; Praveen kumar et al. 2018; Rahbar et al. 2017; Rajaseenivasan et al. 2014) to measure the economy of the modified solar still (Al-Garni 2012a; Chaichan and Kazem 2015; Praveen kumar et al. 2018; Rajaseenivasan et al. 2014, 2016). The techniques were the capital recovery factor (CRF) and the annual/annual/fixed/cost (FAC) factor. The values were calculated as follows:9CRF=i(1+i)N1+iN-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
